<TITLE> Bomb threats sent to police HQs in CHT </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, Oct 5 (bdnews24.com)An extremist Islamic group on Sunday threatened to bomb the office of the police superintendent at Rangamati, claiming to make the attack 100 percent successful, officials said. Rangamati police superintendent Mausd-ul-Huq confirmed bdnews24.com about the threat and said security was tightened in the town as police were not taking the matter lightly. The threat was made through a letter which said all police superintendent offices in the three hill tracts districts would be blown away by conducting bomb operations. Huq said the letter was sent to high officials in Dhaka, who forwarded it to the superintendents of the three hill districts by post and fax. "Police forces have been kept on high alert to guard against any militant attack in the hill districts," Huq said. bdne
